02/11/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A total of 55 parties, or 3,858 candidates will run in the November 25th parliamentary elections. The Central Electoral Commission (CEC) said that as of the deadline Thursday (November 1st), 16 independent candidates and 71 candidates from the national minorities registered. Campaigning officially kicks off on Monday. Croatia's next parliament would be composed of up to 160 members. Eight seats are reserved for representatives of national minorities and up to12 seats are for Croats living abroad. (Vjesnik, Vecernji List - 02/11/07; HRT, HINA, Javno.com, AP - 01/11/07)
